summary: An Ordinance approving the assessment roll of Local Improvement District No. 1327, for the improvement of Twenty-fourth Avenue South, in the City of Seattle, from Norman Street to Atlantic Street, by regrading the same, and by curbing the same, and by constructing concrete walks thereon, under Ordinance No. 14973 and assessing the amounts thereof against each parcel and lot of land and part thereof shown in said roll, and providing for the collection thereof.
